snippet.textDisplay: This video hit hard and true. I have a bad habit of holding onto stuff from my past. I moved in with my husband back in 2013 but there is still a box left unpacked and I'm scared to unbox it because that means I have fully left my old home. I had so much planned to do with this house this year but I lost my granddad in July to cancer and my depression has spiraled. Since then I had bought so much stuff to fill the empty void and mend the heartache but it didnt and sat being wasted. So after watching this video, I packed about 5 bags for the local cancer research charity shop full of all sorts of stuff. Thank you for this Jeffrey, I needed a kick up the butt to get in gear. I hope 2020 brings you and Nate lots of happiness in your new home. Also sick X Files tattoo!
